                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d354">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">835.00/309: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Riddle</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-09-29T12:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 29, 1922—noon</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received 3:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>61. Your 49, September 26, 5 p.m. Argentine Foreign Office states that the
                    President’s letter appointing me special representative at <pb facs="0731"
                        n="611" xml:id="pg_611"/> the inauguration ceremonies of President-elect
                    Alvear should be addressed to President Irigoyen and requests that letter be
                    corrected accordingly. Please instruct.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Riddle</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
